---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Czech Republic Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/czech-republic/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
  { title: 'Poland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/poland' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'czechFit', header: 'Czech Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'PVZP/Maxima', entryAge: '70', renewal: 'To 70', monthlyFrom: 'CZK 4,500-8,000/mo', czechFit: 'Required for Visa' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CZK 8,500-12,000/mo', czechFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CZK 10,000-14,000/mo', czechFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'CZK 7,800-11,000/mo', czechFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Czech Public (VZP)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '13.5% income', czechFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'PVZP Comprehensive (Required)', monthly: 'CZK 4,500-8,000', annual: 'CZK 54,000-96,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'CZK 8,000-12,000', annual: 'CZK 96,000-144,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'CZK 11,000-16,000', annual: 'CZK 132,000-192,000' },
  { category: 'Czech Public Insurance (VZP)', monthly: '13.5% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Czech Private Top-up', monthly: 'CZK 1,000-3,000', annual: 'CZK 12,000-36,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Czech Republic 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Czech Republic. PVZP requirements, Prague hospitals, Zivno visa, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Czech Republic"
  subheadline="Czech Republic offers affordable European living, excellent beer, rich culture, and good healthcare—but specific PVZP insurance is required for long-term visas."
  heroImage="/images/countries/czech-republic-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Czech Republic</h2>
  <p>
    Czech Republic offers an appealing combination: Central European location, rich history, affordable cost of living, and surprisingly good healthcare. Prague is consistently rated one of the world's most beautiful cities, while smaller towns offer even better value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Prague provides cultural richness, excellent healthcare facilities, and vibrant expat community. Brno offers a more local feel with good universities and hospitals. Český Krumlov and smaller towns appeal to those seeking quiet, affordable retirement with adequate healthcare access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good quality; mix of public and private</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Czech; English common in Prague</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> CZK 30,000-50,000/month (~€1,200-2,000)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; cold winters, warm summers</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (not Eurozone; uses CZK)</li>
      <li><strong>Beer:</strong> World's highest per capita consumption; excellent quality</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Czech Republic Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Czech Republic has mandatory health insurance for all residents. The public system (VZP is largest fund) provides comprehensive coverage funded through income-based contributions. Quality is good, with modern hospitals in major cities and competent staff.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is growing, especially in Prague. International clinics cater to expats with English-speaking staff. Wait times in public system can be weeks for specialists; private offers faster access. Dental tourism is popular—quality work at lower prices.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">PVZP Requirement for Non-EU</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Non-EU nationals applying for long-term residence must have "comprehensive health insurance" from a Czech-approved provider—typically PVZP (Pojišťovna VZP) or Maxima. International insurance like SafetyWing is NOT accepted. This is a strict requirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Czech Republic offers several pathways for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Long-Term Residence (Financial Independence)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically CZK 100,000+ bank balance and ongoing income proof). Requires PVZP/Maxima comprehensive health insurance. Valid 1 year, renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Živnostenský List (Trade License)</h3>
  <p>
    Self-employment visa for those with a trade/business. Popular pathway—even minimal freelance work qualifies. Allows access to Czech public health insurance after establishment.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register after 90 days with proof of income and health insurance. Can join Czech public health insurance (VZP) once working or self-employed.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Czech Republic has specific insurance requirements:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Non-EU visa:</strong> PVZP or Maxima "comprehensive" insurance required (NOT international insurers)</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; can join Czech public system</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can switch to public system if employed/self-employed</li>
    <li><strong>International supplement:</strong> Many add for travel and home country coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Czech Republic</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Non-EU nationals MUST use PVZP or Maxima for visa—international insurers are not accepted. Once you have živnostenský list (trade license), you can access Czech public insurance. Many maintain international coverage alongside for travel and potential evacuation to home country.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Czech Republic, provider choice depends on visa status:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Czech Republic</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>PVZP/Maxima:</strong> Required for non-EU visa applications; no alternative</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Supplement for travel and comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), good for complex needs</li>
    <li><strong>Czech VZP:</strong> Public system once eligible; affordable and comprehensive</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare international coverage to supplement PVZP for Czech Republic.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Czech Republic include mandatory PVZP plus optional supplements:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get živnostenský:</strong> Trade license allows Czech public insurance access</li>
    <li><strong>PVZP basic:</strong> Minimum required coverage, add international for gaps</li>
    <li><strong>Age limits:</strong> PVZP comprehensive has age limits (~70); plan accordingly</li>
    <li><strong>Czech public:</strong> Once eligible, 13.5% of income is often cheaper</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Applying for long-term residence in Prague.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> PVZP comprehensive (required). Add Cigna Global for US visits and comprehensive travel coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> PVZP ~CZK 6,000/month + Cigna ~CZK 8,000/month (Czech excluded). Total ~$580/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Digital Nomad, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, getting živnostenský list. Does consulting work.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> PVZP initially for visa. After živnostenský, join Czech public (VZP). Keep BUPA for UK coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Czech public ~13.5% income + BUPA ~CZK 7,000/month (Czech excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EU citizen retiring from Munich to Brno. German pension €1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EHIC initially. Register, can access Czech public system. Add Allianz for Germany and travel.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Czech public ~13.5% pension + Allianz ~CZK 6,000/month (Czech excluded).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use SafetyWing or Cigna for my visa?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No. Czech Republic specifically requires insurance from approved Czech providers—typically PVZP or Maxima. International insurers are NOT accepted for long-term visa applications. This is a common mistake that causes visa rejections.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is the živnostenský list?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        A Czech trade license allowing self-employment. Popular among expats because it provides a residence pathway and access to Czech public health insurance. Even minimal freelance work (consulting, teaching, etc.) qualifies. It's often easier than pure retirement residence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Czech healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Good quality, especially in Prague and Brno. Modern hospitals, competent staff, and improving facilities. Wait times in public system can be weeks for non-urgent care. Private clinics offer faster access. Dental care is excellent value—many Europeans come for dental tourism.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Czech?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In Prague, English is widely spoken in healthcare, business, and daily life. Outside Prague, Czech becomes more important. Administrative processes are in Czech. Learning basic Czech improves daily life significantly and is appreciated by locals.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes for international coverage to supplement required PVZP insurance.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Czech authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
